I am basically already a data scientist without the title but trying to get into the tech world. I‚Äôm on course 6/8 and have mixed feelings about the certificate but overall think it was great and structured well.

Did I need the certificate? Not really, I already knew the technical skills the course offered so I‚Äôm not sure there is any benefit to me putting it on my resume.

Is it still worth taking? I think it is great for someone like me who has a degree that is science related but doesn‚Äôt have professional business experience. Like the guests mentioned it is heavy on the process and decision making. I learned a lot of buzz words and other information that will help me interview well and definitely helped me develop a solid resume.

Is this good for someone with no experience? Absolutely. As someone who already analyzes data and constantly creates methodology, I can say the structure of the course is really about getting you used to thinking analytically. It‚Äôs also a great intro to technical skills although these alone will not get you a job since it‚Äôs a little barebones.

Do I recommend the certificate? Yes but only if you have motivation. If you are serious about a career in data analytics this is a good precursor to your career you just have to want it and have patience. You aren‚Äôt going to want to hear this but this is likely a baby step to getting to that career. You have to continue to develop the technical skills, update your resume, and make a portfolio or git.
